---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Algorithmic Tabletop Program | hackall360"
  description="Security and production readiness drills that exercise AI pipelines, autonomous guardrails, and human escalation choreography."
>
  <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-4xl flex-col gap-12 px-6 py-24 sm:px-10 lg:py-28">
    <header class="space-y-6 text-slate-200">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.5em] text-accent-light/80">// initiative Â· ai tabletop drills</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-5xl">Simulating resilient AI operations.</h1>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-300 sm:text-lg">
        The tabletop track for October and November 2025 steps beyond checklists. Each scenario blends model assurance,
        adversarial security, and production analytics so both human operators and autonomous agents can rehearse recovery
        together.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section id="october-2025" class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-slate-800/60 bg-slate-950/40 p-8 text-slate-200">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="rounded-full border border-accent/40 bg-accent/10 px-3 py-1 text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-accent-light">October 2025</span>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-accent-light/70">Active drills</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Algorithmic readiness game-days</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        Facilitating multi-hour runbooks where security leads, model owners, and SREs co-drive adversarial prompts and
        cascading failure injections. The focus is on validating alignment guardrails, bias regression monitors, and the
        telemetry escaping every AI-assisted workflow.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        <li>Adversarial prompt ladders probe model override pathways and validate grounded response fallbacks.</li>
        <li>Real-time tracing overlays ensure every escalation lands with accountable human ownership.</li>
        <li>Parallel drills explore how AI-assisted runbooks and manual procedures co-exist without deadlocks.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="november-2025" class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-slate-800/60 bg-slate-950/30 p-8 text-slate-200">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="rounded-full border border-accent/40 bg-accent/10 px-3 py-1 text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-accent-light">November 2025</span>
        <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-accent-light/70">Ready queue</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Autonomous incident simulations</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        Evolving the tabletop kits into fully-instrumented simulation sandboxes. Synthetic workloads stress-test autonomous
        remediation bots, compliance policy engines, and the escalation fabric before new AI services leave staging.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        <li>Scenario generators synthesize telemetry spikes and content moderation edge cases to validate guardrails.</li>
        <li>Runbooks grade both human-in-the-loop checkpoints and hands-off automation to ensure parity.</li>
        <li>Post-game analytics feed directly into the AI control plane roadmap for instrumentation gaps.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-slate-800/60 bg-slate-950/40 p-8 text-slate-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Tooling stack</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        Each tabletop kit ships with curated prompts, replayable telemetry captures, and automation harnesses. They hook into
        the same observability runway powering the AI control plane so learnings travel fast between experiments.
      </p>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800/60 bg-slate-950/50 p-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Synthetic workload injector</h3>
          <p>Generates deterministic streams that mimic inference bursts, rogue agents, and policy contention.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800/60 bg-slate-950/50 p-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Operator HUD</h3>
          <p>Unifies traces, escalation timers, and countermeasure toggles so facilitators stay ahead of the simulation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
